Article 5}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(1) The citizens of the German Democratic Republic exercise their political power through democratically elected representative bodies.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(2) The people's representations are the basis of the system of state organs. In their work, they rely on the active participation of the citizens in the preparation, implementation and control of their decisions.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(3) At no time and under no circumstances can organs other than those provided for in the constitution exercise state power.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Article 6}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(1) The German Democratic Republic, true to the interests of the German people and the international obligations of all Germans in its territory, has eradicated German militarism and Nazism and pursues a foreign policy that serves peace and socialism, international understanding and security.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(2) The German Democratic Republic cultivates and develops all-round cooperation and friendship with the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics and the other socialist states in accordance with the principles of socialist internationalism.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(3) The German Democratic Republic supports the aspirations of the peoples for freedom and independence and cultivates cooperation with all states on the basis of equality and mutual respect.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(4) The German Democratic Republic strives for a system of collective security in Europe and a stable peace order in the world. She is committed to general disarmament.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(5) Militaristic and revanchist propaganda in every form, incitement to war and expressions of religious, racial and national hatred are punishable as crimes.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Article 7}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(1) The state organs guarantee the inviolability of the national territory of the German Democratic Republic, including the airspace and territorial waters, as well as the protection and use of the continental shelf.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(2) The German Democratic Republic organizes national defense as well as the protection of the socialist order and the peaceful life of the citizens. The National People's Army and the other organs of national defense protect the socialist achievements of the people against all external attacks. The National People's Army maintains close brotherhood in arms with the armies of the Soviet Union and other socialist states in the interests of maintaining peace and safeguarding the socialist state.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

