  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(1) All state and economic organs are obliged to support the MPs in the performance of their tasks.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(2) The members of the People's Chamber have the rights of immunity. Restrictions on personal freedom, house searches, confiscations or criminal prosecution are only permitted against members of the People's Chamber with the consent of the People's Chamber or in the period between their meetings with the consent of the Council of State. The decision of the Council of State requires confirmation by the People's Chamber.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The members of the People's Chamber are entitled to refuse to testify about persons who entrust them with facts in their capacity as members of parliament or to whom they have entrusted such facts in the exercise of their parliamentary activities, as well as about these facts themselves.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(3) The MPs must not suffer any professional or other personal disadvantages from their membership. They are released from their professional activity insofar as the performance of their duties as members of parliament so requires. Salaries and wages must continue to be paid.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

