(1) The Council of Ministers works on the basis of the laws and resolutions of the People's Chamber as well as the decrees and resolutions of the Council of State. It issues ordinances and resolutions within the framework of laws and decrees.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(2) The Council of Ministers directs, coordinates and controls the activities of the ministries, the other central state organs and the councils of the districts in accordance with the findings of organizational science.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
(3) The Council of Ministers decides on the conclusion and termination of international agreements that are concluded on its behalf.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

